  "body": "### Description\n\nThere is built-in loadbalance support from MySQL Connector/J driver, so we can write `quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:mysql:loadbalance://192.168.32.101,192.168.32.102/dbname` in application.properties to take the advantage of load balance.\r\n\r\nFor reactive mysql client similar config not work because vert.x mysql client not support the `loadbalance` keyword within url. But vert.x do support server load balance. https://vertx.io/docs/vertx-mysql-client/java/#_advanced_pool_configuration\r\n\r\nDo we have any plan to support config like this? `quarkus.datasource.reactive.url=mysql:loadbalance://192.168.32.101,192.168.32.102/dbname`\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nupdate io.quarkus.reactive.mysql.client.runtime.MySQLPoolRecorder, change `MySQLPool.pool(Vertx vertx, MySQLConnectOptions database, PoolOptions options)` to `MySQLPool.pool(Vertx vertx, List<MySQLConnectOptions> databases, PoolOptions options)` if keyword `loadbalance` present in the url",
